* COMMANDS *

$ date :shows the current system time.
$ date +%d-%m-%y :shows the current system Day of month, Month and Year.
$ date -s 14:55 :sets the current time to 14:55.

$ hwclock :shows hardware clock.
$ hwclock --systohc :synchronizes current system time to the hardware clock.
$ hwclock --hctosys :synchronizes current hardware time to the system clock.

$ timedatectl :shows the current time settings.
$ timedatectl status :show current time setting differently.
$ timedatectl list-timezones :list all time zones.
$ timedatectl set-timezone <time-zone> :set a new time zone.
$ timedatectl set-ntp <0/1> :set NTP server, boolean 1=on and 0=off.
_________________________________

* CONFIGURATION DIR/FILES *

/etc/chrony.conf :file that can be configured with a standart list of NTP servers.
